The paper discusses technologies such as mmWave communications, Massive MIMO, and beamforming, which are all related to network infrastructure and communication protocols, indicating a likely category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the use of artificial intelligence-based techniques for interference mitigation and resource allocation, suggesting a possible category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions ultra-low latency and higher data rates, which are related to information theory and signal processing, indicating a possible category of cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses D2D communication, which is related to mobile computing and wireless communication, suggesting a possible category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the use of heterogeneous networks, which are related to control systems and optimization, indicating a possible category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
